.in .5i
.ti -.5i
27.	Unplug the power cord and wait one minute.  Then remove the
shield.  Make sure it is not cutting into any wires and the foil
tape (if present) is not in-between the shield and the circuit board.

Once disassembled, if nothing obvious presents itself, replace the "X"
or "XD" ROM
with the original "C" 
or "D" ROM and repeat Steps 24 and 25 to see if the machine
works correctly.  If so, the "X" or
"XD" ROM you have may be defective and it should
be returned for replacement.  Skip to Step 33 to reassemble your machine.

.ti -.5i
28.	Wait one minute.  You should see the message \fLDiskette?\fR
on the display.  If there is no text on the screen, adjust the
brightness and contrast controls on the left side of the base,
but AVOID TOUCHING ANY WIRES.  Turn both controls to maximum so
that you can see the screen raster (fine lines running horizontally
across the screen.)

If you do not see the message \fLDiskette?\fR, go to Step 26.

.ti -.5i
29.	Press
.bx BREAK
\&.  You should see the \fLCass ?\fR prompt.  (This message may be displayed more than once.
This is normal.)  If not, go to Step 26.

.ti -.5i
30.	Press
.bx ENTER
 at the \fLCass ?\fR prompt.  When the \fLMemory Size?\fR prompt is displayed, press 
.bx ENTER
 again.   You should now be at the \fLREADY\fR prompt.  If not, go to Step 26.

.ti -.5i
31.	Hold the
.bx CTRL
 key down and press
.bx \;
 (semicolon).  If the "X" or "XD" ROM is installed, you should see a caret
(\fL^\fR).  If you do not see
this character, the "X" or "XD" ROM is not installed, so go to Step 27 and check
the installation.

.ti -.5i
32.	If the above checks worked correctly, the "X" or "XD" ROM installation is correct.  Now unplug the
power cord and wait one minute.
If you performed these tests as directed in Step 34, go back to Step 34.
Otherwise, reassemble the computer by following the instructions below.  


\s+2Reassemble the Computer\s-2

.ti -.5i
33.	Make sure the power cord is unplugged.    From the front of the
machine, lift the cover and place it over the computer base.
Watch the neck of CRT through the top vents or through the
top floppy drive opening in the cover.  The cover should be guided
so that the CRT neck does not strike the CPU enclosure and does
not hang on any of the wires that are routed near the CRT.
If the CRT socket won't clear the wires, remove the cover and
adjust the wiring so that the CRT and its socket have more room.
If you have a second person to help, they should assist in guiding
the cover into position.

.ti -.5i
34.	Now, go to Step 24 and perform the "X" or "XD" ROM tests.
If a problem is encountered, remove the cover (see Step 9)
and check the items covered in Step 27.

If the "X" or "XD" ROM tests were successful, continue with Step 35.


.ti -.5i
35.	Unplug the computer and replace the screw in the back of the cover.
Then set the machine on its side and install the 10 screws that
came from the bottom.  Be sure you get them back in the right
holes.  Tighten but do not force as these bolts are going into
plastic and can be easily stripped.


.in 0i
This completes the installation of the "X" or "XD" ROM.














